<fn-group>
  <fn id="fn1">
    <label>1</label><p>ffigen: bindings generator for FFI bindings.
    <ext-link ext-link-type="uri" xlink:href="https://pub.dev/packages/ffigen">https://pub.dev/packages/ffigen</ext-link>.</p>
  </fn>
  <fn id="fn2">
    <label>2</label><p>Raw data and source code used for generating the
    figures and statistics are available at:
    <ext-link ext-link-type="uri" xlink:href="https://github.com/NexusDynamic/liblsl.dart/tree/main/packages/liblsl/paper/analysis">https://github.com/NexusDynamic/liblsl.dart/tree/main/packages/liblsl/paper/analysis</ext-link>.</p>
  </fn>
  <fn id="fn3">
    <label>3</label><p>In a lab context, this typically may be achieved
    by using a closed, wired network, with a high throughput hardware
    switch or router, and by disabling firewalls, traffic shaping and
    other features that may introduce latency such as deep packet
    inspection.</p>
  </fn>
  <fn id="fn4">
    <label>4</label><p>Merged and pending pull requests by author Luke
    Ring (@zeyus) for the <monospace>liblsl</monospace> repository:
    <ext-link ext-link-type="uri" xlink:href="https://github.com/sccn/liblsl/pulls?q=is%3Apr+author%3Azeyus">https://github.com/sccn/liblsl/pulls?q=is%3Apr+author%3Azeyus</ext-link>.</p>
  </fn>
